    <node id="Cholesterol">
      <data key="d0">Cholesterol</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Cholesterol is a variable measured in mg/100 cc that is correlated with risk.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-cc71e0306c5c259756e6206620a858b1</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776188621</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Risk">
      <data key="d0">Risk</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Risk is the measure of potential health outcomes that depends on both cholesterol and blood pressure levels.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-cc71e0306c5c259756e6206620a858b1</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776188621</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Bivariate Normal Model">
      <data key="d0">Bivariate Normal Model</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">The model is a statistical tool used to summarize the joint dependence of risk on cholesterol and blood pressure.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-cc71e0306c5c259756e6206620a858b1</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776188622</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Equation 7">
      <data key="d0">Equation 7</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Equation 7 is a mathematical formula used to describe the association between risk and changes in cholesterol and blood pressure.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-cc71e0306c5c259756e6206620a858b1</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776188622</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Expected Number Of CHD Cases">
      <data key="d0">Expected Number Of CHD Cases</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">This data represents the anticipated number of new Coronary Heart Disease cases, compared against actual observations.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-cc71e0306c5c259756e6206620a858b1</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776188622</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Percentage Change">
      <data key="d0">Percentage Change</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Percentage change is a calculation method used to determine the difference in risk relative to the initial level, often independent of the starting point.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-cc71e0306c5c259756e6206620a858b1</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776188622</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Absolute Change">
      <data key="d0">Absolute Change</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Absolute change is a calculation method describing how the change in risk depends on the level from which the change takes place.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-cc71e0306c5c259756e6206620a858b1</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776188622</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="X1">
      <data key="d0">X1</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">X1 is the data input representing serum cholesterol levels in mg/100 cc, used in the risk calculation formula.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-cc71e0306c5c259756e6206620a858b1</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776188622</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="X2">
      <data key="d0">X2</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">X2 is the data input representing systolic blood pressure levels in mm Hg, used in the risk calculation formula.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-cc71e0306c5c259756e6206620a858b1</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776188623</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="L-Year Risk">
      <data key="d0">L-Year Risk</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">The l-year risk is a measurement derived as one-sixth of the 6-year risk.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-cc71e0306c5c259756e6206620a858b1</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776188623</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="mg/100 cc">
      <data key="d0">mg/100 cc</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">The unit of measurement for serum cholesterol levels.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-cc71e0306c5c259756e6206620a858b1</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776188623</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="mm Hg">
      <data key="d0">mm Hg</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">The unit of measurement for systolic blood pressure levels.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-cc71e0306c5c259756e6206620a858b1</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776188623</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Log Normal Distribution">
      <data key="d0">Log Normal Distribution</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">The log normal distribution is an excellent theoretical distribution proposed to characterize the relationship between cholesterol levels in both CHD and NCHD populations.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-baa95425f9536fc6e61a6ea35b2d5490</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776188624</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Risk Function P(Y)">
      <data key="d0">Risk Function P(Y)</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">The risk function P(Y) denotes the proportion of individuals with serum cholesterol of Y that belong to the CHD population.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-baa95425f9536fc6e61a6ea35b2d5490</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776188624</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Bivariate Normal Frequency Function">
      <data key="d0">Bivariate Normal Frequency Function</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">This function is used to characterize both the CHD and NCHD populations simultaneously using log10 cholesterol and log10 (blood pressure – 75).</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-baa95425f9536fc6e61a6ea35b2d5490</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776188624</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Framingham">
      <data key="d0">Framingham</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">The Framingham analysis provided initial results regarding CHD and NCHD distributions, particularly concerning cholesterol and blood pressure.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-baa95425f9536fc6e61a6ea35b2d5490</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776188624</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Proportion P">
      <data key="d0">Proportion P</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">Proportion P represents the probability of an individual belonging to the CHD population, calculated as 92/1329.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-baa95425f9536fc6e61a6ea35b2d5490</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776188624</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Log10 Blood Pressure Adjusted">
      <data key="d0">Log10 Blood Pressure Adjusted</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">Log10 (blood pressure – 75) is the base-10 logarithm of blood pressure minus 75, serving as a key variable in the bivariate frequency distribution models.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-baa95425f9536fc6e61a6ea35b2d5490</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776188624</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Jerome Cornfield">
      <data key="d0">Jerome Cornfield</data>
      <data key="d1">person</data>
      <data key="d2">Jerome Cornfield is the author of the paper describing the joint dependence of coronary heart disease risk on serum cholesterol and systolic blood pressure.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-2a698820f9767612065e4d08199917ba</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776188625</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Coronary Heart Disease">
      <data key="d0">Coronary Heart Disease</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Coronary Heart Disease is the disease whose risk is being analyzed based on serum cholesterol and systolic blood pressure levels.&lt;SEP&gt;Coronary heart disease is described as a serious public health problem with a multifactorial etiology.&lt;SEP&gt;Coronary heart disease is a health risk increased by central obesity, type 1 and type 2 diabetes, and smoking.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-2a698820f9767612065e4d08199917ba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1402c215c7fd318145880a62d19e2b3a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8c2d4bf173facbfeaa65d8b86b3d62ca</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190136</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Discriminant Function Analysis">
      <data key="d0">Discriminant Function Analysis</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Discriminant Function Analysis is a mathematical method used to summarize observations and model the joint dependence of CHD risk on cholesterol and blood pressure.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-2a698820f9767612065e4d08199917ba</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776188625</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Framingham, Massachusetts">
      <data key="d0">Framingham, Massachusetts</data>
      <data key="d1">location</data>
      <data key="d2">Framingham, Massachusetts is the location where the long-term follow-up study of heart disease was conducted.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-2a698820f9767612065e4d08199917ba</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776188625</data>
