    </node>
    <node id="Federation Proceedings">
      <data key="d0">Federation Proceedings</data>
      <data key="d1">event</data>
      <data key="d2">Federation Proceedings is the source publication where the paper was presented in July-August 1962.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-2a698820f9767612065e4d08199917ba</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776188626</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Myocardial Infarction">
      <data key="d0">Myocardial Infarction</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Myocardial infarction is a clinically manifest form of coronary heart disease developed in the study sample.&lt;SEP&gt;Myocardial infarction is a significant medical event requiring long-term treatment with aspirin and beta-adrenergic blockers.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-2a698820f9767612065e4d08199917ba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a512cd818fc7fc052ba42676e3dbd8a6</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190057</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Angina Pectoris">
      <data key="d0">Angina Pectoris</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Angina pectoris is a clinically manifest form of coronary heart disease developed in the study sample.&lt;SEP&gt;A chest pain condition that can be effectively treated by calcium antagonists, primarily by relieving vasospastic angina.&lt;SEP&gt;Angina pectoris is mentioned as the most common initial manifestation of chronic ischaemic heart disease.&lt;SEP&gt;Angina Pectoris is a symptom whose threshold is assessed and which can be managed by therapy to improve quality of life.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-2a698820f9767612065e4d08199917ba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5d706ae189b3bf78b45c9dc1e1b73ebf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0a8a07023292447dd472b098aca92a15&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-725fd25b2b914218473f4027eb936a0b</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190050</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="6-Year Risk">
      <data key="d0">6-Year Risk</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-cc71e0306c5c259756e6206620a858b1</data>
      <data key="d2">The l-year risk is defined by its mathematical relationship to the 6-year risk, specifically being one-sixth of it.</data>
      <data key="d1">UNKNOWN</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776188631</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Calcium Antagonists">
      <data key="d0">Calcium Antagonists</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">A class of drugs used to treat hypertension and angina pectoris, which decreases coronary vascular resistance and increases coronary blood flow.&lt;SEP&gt;Calcium antagonists are a class of drugs that effectively treat hypertension and angina pectoris by decreasing coronary vascular resistance.&lt;SEP&gt;Calcium antagonists, including verapamil and diltiazem, are medications used for cardiac treatment, especially if beta-blockers are contraindicated.&lt;SEP&gt;Calcium antagonists may be selectively prescribed in patients with specific indications such as hypertension or angina.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5d706ae189b3bf78b45c9dc1e1b73ebf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a512cd818fc7fc052ba42676e3dbd8a6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ba47882bd330c094f4cf8a1a605cf0b0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0a8a07023292447dd472b098aca92a15</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190050</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Dihydropyridine">
      <data key="d0">Dihydropyridine</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">One of the common classes of calcium antagonists used for treating conditions like hypertension and angina pectoris.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5d706ae189b3bf78b45c9dc1e1b73ebf</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190050</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Nondihydropyridine">
      <data key="d0">Nondihydropyridine</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">One of the common classes of calcium antagonists used for treating conditions like hypertension and angina pectoris.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5d706ae189b3bf78b45c9dc1e1b73ebf</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190050</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Hypertension">
      <data key="d0">Hypertension</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">A chronic condition characterized by high blood pressure and listed as a modifiable risk factor for cardiovascular disease.&lt;SEP&gt;Hypertension is a major cardiovascular risk factor, a contraindication, and a condition treated by certain medications.&lt;SEP&gt;Hypertension is defined by a blood pressure exceeding 170/100 mmHg, indicating a high-risk condition for severe ACS.&lt;SEP&gt;Hypertension is a health condition with recorded prevalence rates in adults aged 25 and above.&lt;SEP&gt;Hypertension is a risk factor associated with central obesity, potentially leading to increased coronary artery disease.&lt;SEP&gt;Hypertension (HBP) is a risk factor requiring blood pressure control goals (≤ 140/90 mmHg).&lt;SEP&gt;Hypertension is a specific indication that might warrant the selective prescription of calcium antagonists.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5d706ae189b3bf78b45c9dc1e1b73ebf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a512cd818fc7fc052ba42676e3dbd8a6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e6bcb6c446cca77c7de2fbf5c07b59b0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1402c215c7fd318145880a62d19e2b3a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8c2d4bf173facbfeaa65d8b86b3d62ca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0a8a07023292447dd472b098aca92a15&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fba062a869c808ddf245e61a4921a0b9</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190050</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Coronary Artery Disease (CAD)">
      <data key="d0">Coronary Artery Disease (CAD)</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">A serious disease state whose risk factors, such as smoking and hyperlipidemia, are modifiable and affect clinical outcome.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5d706ae189b3bf78b45c9dc1e1b73ebf</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190050</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Obesity">
      <data key="d0">Obesity</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">A common condition associated with an increased risk for CAD and mortality, contributing to other coronary risk factors.&lt;SEP&gt;Obesity is a condition that can be assessed by measures such as Body Mass Index, Waist Hip Ratio, and Waist Circumference.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5d706ae189b3bf78b45c9dc1e1b73ebf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1402c215c7fd318145880a62d19e2b3a</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190050</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Beta-blockers">
      <data key="d0">Beta-blockers</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">A class of drugs that may be used in combination with or substituted for calcium antagonists for initial angina therapy.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5d706ae189b3bf78b45c9dc1e1b73ebf</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190050</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Verapamil">
      <data key="d0">Verapamil</data>
      <data key="d1">drug</data>
      <data key="d2">A specific calcium antagonist that reduces myocardial oxygen demand by decreasing heart rate and contractility.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5d706ae189b3bf78b45c9dc1e1b73ebf</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190052</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Diltiazem">
      <data key="d0">Diltiazem</data>
      <data key="d1">drug</data>
      <data key="d2">A specific calcium antagonist that reduces myocardial oxygen demand by decreasing heart rate and contractility.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5d706ae189b3bf78b45c9dc1e1b73ebf</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190052</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Fibrate Gemfibrozil">
      <data key="d0">Fibrate Gemfibrozil</data>
      <data key="d1">drug</data>
      <data key="d2">A drug that was demonstrated in a randomized trial to reduce cardiovascular mortality in patients with CAD.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5d706ae189b3bf78b45c9dc1e1b73ebf</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190053</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="World Health Organisation">
      <data key="d0">World Health Organisation</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">The international body responsible for health standards, featured on the document source citation.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Health Organisation is an organization listed in the context header related to medical care standards.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Health Organisation is listed as a source for health information regarding coronary artery disease prevention.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Health Organisation is an organization that recommends the Body Mass Index for assessing the degree of obesity.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5d706ae189b3bf78b45c9dc1e1b73ebf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-41d9481df9dca8a996f49a342af0df96&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1402c215c7fd318145880a62d19e2b3a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8c2d4bf173facbfeaa65d8b86b3d62ca</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190053</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Mini-Invasive Heart">
      <data key="d0">Mini-Invasive Heart</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">The core area of study related to treating and managing conditions like CAD, focused on prevention and risk reduction.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5d706ae189b3bf78b45c9dc1e1b73ebf</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190053</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Medicare">
      <data key="d0">Medicare</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Placeholder for a clinical outcome measure or system related to patient care standards.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5d706ae189b3bf78b45c9dc1e1b73ebf</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190053</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Diabetes Mellitus">
      <data key="d0">Diabetes Mellitus</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">A modifiable coronary disease risk factor that, alongside smoking and hypertension, is common in patients with chronic ischaemic heart disease.&lt;SEP&gt;Diabetes Mellitus is a health condition with recorded prevalence rates in adults aged 25 and above.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5d706ae189b3bf78b45c9dc1e1b73ebf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8c2d4bf173facbfeaa65d8b86b3d62ca</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190053</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Hyperlipidemia">
      <data key="d0">Hyperlipidemia</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">A modifiable coronary disease risk factor that is associated with elevated triglycerides and low HDL cholesterol.&lt;SEP&gt;Hyperlipidemia is identified as a cardiac risk factor that requires control to aid in secondary prevention of ACS.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5d706ae189b3bf78b45c9dc1e1b73ebf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e6bcb6c446cca77c7de2fbf5c07b59b0</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190054</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Cigarette Smoking">
      <data key="d0">Cigarette Smoking</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">A modifiable coronary disease risk factor that increases the risk of death from CAD.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5d706ae189b3bf78b45c9dc1e1b73ebf</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190054</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="HDL Cholesterol">
      <data key="d0">HDL Cholesterol</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">A measure of cholesterol level; low levels are associated with increased CAD risk.&lt;SEP&gt;High-density lipoprotein (HDL) cholesterol is measured for lipid management, with a recommended value of &gt; 35 mg/dl.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5d706ae189b3bf78b45c9dc1e1b73ebf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fba062a869c808ddf245e61a4921a0b9</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190054</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Triglycerides">
      <data key="d0">Triglycerides</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">A type of fat in the blood; elevated levels are associated with increased CAD risk.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5d706ae189b3bf78b45c9dc1e1b73ebf</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190054</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Systemic Vascular Resistance">
      <data key="d0">Systemic Vascular Resistance</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">A physiological measure whose reduction is a primary mechanism by which certain calcium antagonists decrease myocardial oxygen demand.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5d706ae189b3bf78b45c9dc1e1b73ebf</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190054</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Diuretics">
      <data key="d0">Diuretics</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">A class of medication, such as Furosemide, used in the therapy for Congestive Heart Failure.&lt;SEP&gt;Diuretics are recommended to initiate therapy for congestive heart failure.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a512cd818fc7fc052ba42676e3dbd8a6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3bade9898b872aa7e3336771b6b88e1d</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190055</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Nitrates">
      <data key="d0">Nitrates</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">Nitrates are part of the recommended therapy for congestive heart failure and recurrent angina.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a512cd818fc7fc052ba42676e3dbd8a6</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190055</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Positive Inotropic Agents">
      <data key="d0">Positive Inotropic Agents</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">Positive inotropic agents, such as Dobutamine and Dopamine, are used in the therapy for congestive heart failure.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a512cd818fc7fc052ba42676e3dbd8a6</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190055</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Dobutamine">
      <data key="d0">Dobutamine</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">A positive inotropic agent used in therapy for severe heart failure.&lt;SEP&gt;Dobutamine is a positive inotropic agent used intravenously in the treatment of congestive heart failure.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a512cd818fc7fc052ba42676e3dbd8a6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3bade9898b872aa7e3336771b6b88e1d</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190055</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Dopamine">
      <data key="d0">Dopamine</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">A positive inotropic agent used in therapy for severe heart failure.&lt;SEP&gt;Dopamine is a positive inotropic agent used intravenously in the treatment of congestive heart failure.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a512cd818fc7fc052ba42676e3dbd8a6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3bade9898b872aa7e3336771b6b88e1d</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190055</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Swan-Ganz Pulmonary Artery Catheter">
      <data key="d0">Swan-Ganz Pulmonary Artery Catheter</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">A specialized catheter used to monitor pulmonary artery pressures in severe cardiac cases.&lt;SEP&gt;The Swan-Ganz catheter is a device placed in patients with severe ventricular dysfunction or cardiogenic shock to measure multiple physiological resistances and output.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a512cd818fc7fc052ba42676e3dbd8a6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3bade9898b872aa7e3336771b6b88e1d</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190056</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Aspirin">
      <data key="d0">Aspirin</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">Aspirin is a common drug given to all patients with suspected ACS unless contraindicated.&lt;SEP&gt;Aspirin is a foundational agent and a mainstay used in the treatment of ACS.&lt;SEP&gt;A drug administered immediately upon the patient's arrival in the emergency ward for acute MI.&lt;SEP&gt;A drug administered as early adjunctive therapy to prevent thromboxane A2 and prostacyclin production in platelets and endothelial cells.&lt;SEP&gt;Aspirin is recommended for long-term treatment of myocardial infarction and recurrent angina.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a512cd818fc7fc052ba42676e3dbd8a6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-41d9481df9dca8a996f49a342af0df96&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3bade9898b872aa7e3336771b6b88e1d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e6bcb6c446cca77c7de2fbf5c07b59b0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ba47882bd330c094f4cf8a1a605cf0b0</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190056</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Beta-Adrenergic Blockers">
      <data key="d0">Beta-Adrenergic Blockers</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">A class of drugs used to reduce myocardial oxygen consumption and lower morbidity rates.&lt;SEP&gt;Beta-adrenergic blockers are recommended for long-term treatment of myocardial infarction and recurrent angina.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a512cd818fc7fc052ba42676e3dbd8a6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3bade9898b872aa7e3336771b6b88e1d</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
