    <node id="Intravenous Nitroglycerin">
      <data key="d0">Intravenous Nitroglycerin</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">Intravenous nitroglycerin is recommended for treating recurrent angina.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a512cd818fc7fc052ba42676e3dbd8a6</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190056</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Heparin">
      <data key="d0">Heparin</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">Heparin is an anticoagulant therapy used in ACS management, requiring monitoring of KPTT.&lt;SEP&gt;A blood-thinning medication recommended for patients with specific forms of MI or thrombus.&lt;SEP&gt;Heparin is recommended as</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a512cd818fc7fc052ba42676e3dbd8a6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3bade9898b872aa7e3336771b6b88e1d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ba47882bd330c094f4cf8a1a605cf0b0</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190056</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Furosemide">
      <data key="d0">Furosemide</data>
      <data key="d1">drug</data>
      <data key="d2">Furosemide is a diuretic used in the treatment of congestive heart failure.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a512cd818fc7fc052ba42676e3dbd8a6</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190056</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Oxygen">
      <data key="d0">Oxygen</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">A substance administered by nasal prongs or masks to acute MI patients.&lt;SEP&gt;Oxygen is a therapy component recommended for congestive heart failure.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a512cd818fc7fc052ba42676e3dbd8a6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-41d9481df9dca8a996f49a342af0df96</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190057</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Analgesics">
      <data key="d0">Analgesics</data>
      <data key="d1">drug</data>
      <data key="d2">Analgesics are recommended for treating recurrent angina.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a512cd818fc7fc052ba42676e3dbd8a6</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190057</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="ACE Inhibitors">
      <data key="d0">ACE Inhibitors</data>
      <data key="d1">drug</data>
      <data key="d2">A drug class that should be initiated early in patients with acute MI to improve left ventricular function.&lt;SEP&gt;ACE Inhibitors are recommended as part of secondary prevention in patients with left ventricular dysfunction.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a512cd818fc7fc052ba42676e3dbd8a6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3bade9898b872aa7e3336771b6b88e1d</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190057</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Carvedilol">
      <data key="d0">Carvedilol</data>
      <data key="d1">drug</data>
      <data key="d2">Carvedilol has been shown to attenuate ventricular remodeling in patients with left ventricular dysfunction after MI.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a512cd818fc7fc052ba42676e3dbd8a6</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190057</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Congestive Heart Failure">
      <data key="d0">Congestive Heart Failure</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Congestive heart failure is a condition requiring initial therapy with diuretics, nitrates, and oxygen.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a512cd818fc7fc052ba42676e3dbd8a6</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190057</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Left Ventricular Dysfunction">
      <data key="d0">Left Ventricular Dysfunction</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Left ventricular dysfunction is a medical condition requiring secondary prevention using ACE inhibitors and monitoring for drug effects.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a512cd818fc7fc052ba42676e3dbd8a6</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190058</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Angina">
      <data key="d0">Angina</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Angina is a symptom of myocardial oxygen demand exceeding supply, and it can manifest as stable angina or unstable angina.&lt;SEP&gt;Angina refers to the status of pain that can present as new-onset, increasing severity, or post-infarction.&lt;SEP&gt;Angina is a symptom that requires treatment with intravenous nitroglycerin and is monitored with calcium antagonists.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a512cd818fc7fc052ba42676e3dbd8a6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-66cab5fae30b68ce441cbeaea72167d4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ba47882bd330c094f4cf8a1a605cf0b0</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190058</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Cardiovascular Disease">
      <data key="d0">Cardiovascular Disease</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">CVD is the central condition addressed in the guidelines, detailing risk factor reduction and interventions.&lt;SEP&gt;Cardiovascular disease is a major global public health concern with rising mortality rates worldwide.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a512cd818fc7fc052ba42676e3dbd8a6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fba062a869c808ddf245e61a4921a0b9</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190058</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Coronary Artery Disease">
      <data key="d0">Coronary Artery Disease</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">A general concept referring to the condition where the coronary arteries are affected, ranging from stable to acute syndromes.&lt;SEP&gt;Coronary artery disease is identified as the primary non-communicable health problem in Mauritius.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a512cd818fc7fc052ba42676e3dbd8a6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-66cab5fae30b68ce441cbeaea72167d4</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190058</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Mauritius">
      <data key="d0">Mauritius</data>
      <data key="d1">location</data>
      <data key="d2">Mauritius is the location where Coronary Artery Disease is identified as a primary non-communicable health problem.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a512cd818fc7fc052ba42676e3dbd8a6</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190059</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Primary Care Physician">
      <data key="d0">Primary Care Physician</data>
      <data key="d1">person</data>
      <data key="d2">The primary care physician is responsible for preliminary diagnosis, risk stratification, and initial management of patients.&lt;SEP&gt;A medical doctor who may co-manage patients with a cardiologist.&lt;SEP&gt;The primary care physician is responsible for regularly checking for risk factors such as smoking and elevated lipid levels.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a512cd818fc7fc052ba42676e3dbd8a6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-41d9481df9dca8a996f49a342af0df96&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-725fd25b2b914218473f4027eb936a0b</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190059</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
