    <node id="Stages Of Change Model">
      <data key="d0">Stages Of Change Model</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">The Stages of Change Model is a theory proposing that behavioral modification requires assessing an individual's readiness to change.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-4a07b3f1da8427b5b209e9546fe4fc9d</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190145</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Pre-Contemplation">
      <data key="d0">Pre-Contemplation</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Pre-contemplation is the initial stage where individuals do not intend to change their high-risk behavior in the foreseeable future.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-4a07b3f1da8427b5b209e9546fe4fc9d</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190146</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Contemplation">
      <data key="d0">Contemplation</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Contemplation is the stage where people seriously intend to change their behavior but often stay in this stage for extended periods due to ambivalence.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-4a07b3f1da8427b5b209e9546fe4fc9d</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190146</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Preparation Action">
      <data key="d0">Preparation Action</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Preparation action is one of the five proposed stages of behavioral change.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-4a07b3f1da8427b5b209e9546fe4fc9d</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190146</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Maintenance">
      <data key="d0">Maintenance</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Maintenance is one of the five proposed stages of behavioral change, indicating the sustained lifestyle change.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-4a07b3f1da8427b5b209e9546fe4fc9d</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190146</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Chronic Ischaemic Heart Disease">
      <data key="d0">Chronic Ischaemic Heart Disease</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">This is the primary condition requiring multifactorial intervention, regular follow-up, and medical management.&lt;SEP&gt;Chronic Ischaemic Heart Disease is the underlying condition treated by the discussed medical therapies, aiming to prevent MI and death.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-0a8a07023292447dd472b098aca92a15&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-725fd25b2b914218473f4027eb936a0b</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190147</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Chest Pain">
      <data key="d0">Chest Pain</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Chest Pain is a symptom that requires differential diagnosis evaluation in patients suspected of having IHD.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-0a8a07023292447dd472b098aca92a15</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190147</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Myocardial Infarction (MI)">
      <data key="d0">Myocardial Infarction (MI)</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Myocardial Infarction (MI) is a major event that treatment strategies aim to prevent in patients with IHD.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-0a8a07023292447dd472b098aca92a15</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190147</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Beta-Blockers">
      <data key="d0">Beta-Blockers</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">Beta-blockers are a class of drugs used to decrease heart rate, contractility, and arterial pressure for treating angina and hypertension.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-0a8a07023292447dd472b098aca92a15</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190147</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Severe Aortic Stenosis">
      <data key="d0">Severe Aortic Stenosis</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Severe aortic stenosis is listed as a primary cardiac disorder and an absolute contraindication for EST.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-0a8a07023292447dd472b098aca92a15</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190147</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Hypertrophic Obstructive Cardiomyopathy (HOCM)">
      <data key="d0">Hypertrophic Obstructive Cardiomyopathy (HOCM)</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">HOCM is listed as a primary cardiac disorder and an absolute contraindication for EST.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-0a8a07023292447dd472b098aca92a15</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190147</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Coronary Revascularization">
      <data key="d0">Coronary Revascularization</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Coronary revascularization is one of two treatment methods for IHD, alongside medical therapy.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-0a8a07023292447dd472b098aca92a15</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776190148</data>
      <data key="d6" />
